'''Cecilio Alfonso Waterman Ruiz''' (born 13 April 1991) is a Panamanian professional [[association footballer|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker (association football)|striker]] for Chilean club [[C.D. Universidad de Concepción|Universidad de Concepción]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
Waterman made his professional debut with [[Sporting San Miguelito]] on 26 September 2010 in a match against [[Atlético Chiriquí]] in Panama.

In mid-2011, he was transferred to the Uruguayan club [[Centro Atlético Fénix]], where he scored his first goal in May 2012 against Racing.<ref>[http://panamafutbol.com/?p=8237 Baloy juega hoy la final – Waterman con primer gol] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304084225/http://panamafutbol.com/?p=8237 |date=4 March 2016 }} - PanamaFutbol {{in lang|es}}</ref>

In 2022 and 2023, he played for [[Chilean Primera División]] club [[C.D. Cobresal|Cobresal]], finishing as runners-up in the 2023 season.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sánchez |first1=Francisco |title=Una figura del fútbol chileno dice adiós |url=https://chile.as.com/futbol/una-figura-del-futbol-chileno-dice-adios-n/ |access-date=19 December 2023 |work=[[Diario AS]] |date=18 December 2023 |language=es}}</ref>

One year later, he signed with Peruvian club [[Club Alianza Lima|Alianza Lima]] to play in the [[2024 Liga 1 (Peru)|2024 Liga 1]] season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.encancha.cl/futbol-chileno/primera/2023/12/29/exclusivo-cecilio-waterman-deja-el-futbol-chileno-y-es-nuevo-refuerzo-de-alianza-lima/|title=EXCLUSIVO {{!}} Cecilio Waterman deja el fútbol chileno y es nuevo refuerzo de Alianza Lima|access-date=29 December 2023|date=29 December 2023|website=En Cancha|language=es-ch}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Galiano|first=Renzo|title=Alianza Lima halló a su ‘9′ para el 2024: Cecilio Waterman llegó a Perú para firmar su contrato|url=https://www.infobae.com/peru/2024/01/03/alianza-lima-hallo-a-su-9-para-el-2024-cecilio-waterman-llego-a-peru-para-firmar-su-contrato/|date=2 January 2024|language=es|website=[[Infobae]]|access-date=3 January 2024}}</ref>

In 2025, Waterman returned to Chile to join [[Coquimbo Unido]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Cecilio Waterman se sumó a la tripulación pirata |url=https://www.miradiols.cl/2025/01/13/cecilio-waterman-se-sumo-a-la-tripulacion-pirata/ |access-date=14 January 2025 |work=Mi Radio |date=13 January 2025 |language=es}}</ref> contributing to the club's first [[Chilean Primera División|Chilean top-flight title]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=27 October 2025 |title=🏴‍☠ Pirate love: Coquimbo Unido, Chile's underdogs making history |url=https://onefootball.com/fr/news/pirate-love-coquimbo-unido-chiles-underdogs-making-history-41874689 |access-date=3 November 2025 |website=OneFootball |language=}}</ref> He left them at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |title=La nueva salida que remece a Coquimbo Unido: "Ojalá en algún momento nuestros caminos se vuelvan a encontrar" |url=https://www.24horas.cl/deportes/futbol-nacional/cecilio-waterman-comunica-su-salida-de-coquimbo-unido- |access-date=10 December 2025 |work=[[24 horas (Chilean TV program)|24 horas]] |date=10 December 2025 |language=es}}</ref>

On 25 December 2025, Waterman returned to [[C.D. Universidad de Concepción|Universidad de Concepción]] after his stint in 2020–21.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Concha |first1=Julián |title=Regalos de Navidad: U. de Concepción anuncia el regreso Cecilio Waterman y Deportes Concepción da el golpe con Leonardo Valencia |url=https://www.latercera.com/el-deportivo/noticia/regalos-de-navidad-u-de-concepcion-anuncia-el-regreso-cecilio-waterman-y-deportes-concepcion-da-el-golpe-con-leonardo-valencia/ |access-date=25 December 2025 |work=[[La Tercera]] |date=25 December 2025 |language=es}}</ref>

==International career==
Waterman was part of the [[Panama national football team|Panama U-20]] squad for the [[2011 CONCACAF U-20 Championship]] where he scored four goals helping his country qualify to the [[2011 FIFA U-20 World Cup|Youth World Cup]] in Colombia.<ref>{{FIFA player|337251}}</ref>

He made his senior debut for [[Panama national football team|Panama]] in a December 2010 [[friendly match]] against [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]] and has, as of 15 August 2015, earned a total of 7 caps, scoring no goals. In 2013, he was called up by [[Julio Dely Valdés]] to play the [[2013 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].

On 20 March 2025 Waterman scored a late winning goal against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]], taking Panama to the final of the [[2024–25 CONCACAF Nations League|CONCACAF Nations League]] for the first time in their history after losing two prior semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Panama stun USMNT with stoppage-time winner to reach Nations League final |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/mar/20/usa-panama-nations-league-semifinal-waterman-goal |access-date=21 March 2025}}</ref>

